        "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
        "body": "There's no way to accomplish this behavior in a hash based groupby without significant performance loss. For min/max, we rely on CUDA `atomicMin`/`atomicMax`. There's no way to inject custom logic into these comparisons. So we would instead have to specialize floating point min/max operations to use a `atomicCAS` instead, which is much slower than a native `min/max` atomic. \r\n\r\nSort-based groupby uses the same `aggregate_row` functionality for min/max, so it has the same problem. ",
